2 NOTE In a deed abstract was granted 400 acres by the Lord's Proprietors on March 1711.  In April 18, 1733 he made off a mortgage to two merchants for payment on 410 acres.  Sum was 1000 pounds.  He was more than moderately successful for the time.
1 WILL
2 DATE May 19, 1736
2 PLAC Colleton County, South Carolina, USA
2 NOTE He raised cattle and engaged in planting.  Wills lists 136 head of cattle, 20 horses, 55 hogs, miscellaneous furniture and household goods.
