1 _OID 07945bc6-c7cb-4c5e-84ee-c5727d1936f7
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>Kentucky Ancestors - Vol 11 1975&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;p133  Arabia Brown of Garrard county KY - from his newspaper obituary&lt;br&gt;Arabia Brown died Wed 13 March 1844 aged 89. He was a soldier of the Revolution, a nativ
2 CONC e of Virginia and one of the first settlers of Kentucky. He engaged in a number of bloody skirmishes with Indians and was at the siege of Boonsboro. He was kind and liberal of heart and correct in his dealings. He was a member of the Presbyterian C
2 CONC hurch. His wife was Elizabeth Dooley sister of Moses Dooley.&lt;br&gt;Arabia helped Daniel Boone to cut the trail from Cumberland Gap to Boonesboro. Arabia was in Kentucky by 1791 and purchased over 1000 acres of land in Buckeye Fork of Sugar Creek
2 CONC . He enlisted in the Revolutionary War in 1777 in Bedford co VA under Captain Charles Watkins and was sent to Kentucky to act as Indian lookout at the fort there.&lt;br&gt;He was born 27 nov 1755 and married Elizabeth Dooley May 1778. His childre
2 CONC n were Stephen Brown, born 26 June 1779 and went to Missouri, Arabia J Brown junior, Harvey Brown who married Patience Owsley and others whose names were not listed.</line></content></metadataxml>
