2 TITL Old Rappahannock County Deed Books
1 _OID 3edbf163-3d19-4a9f-bd23-0c310245d572
1 PLAC http://lewis187.home.mchsi.com/Lewis/Branham-99.htm#a
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;Married before 1688 in Rappahannock (now Richmond) Co VA to Deborah Haslock b. c. 1645 in England &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt
2 CONC ;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;5/4/1669 Rappahannock (now Richmond) Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Old Rappahannock County Deed Book (16
2 CONC 68-1672), p 76-77:&lt;br&gt;4 May 1669. Thomas Freshwater by virtue of the power he had from his brother-in-law &lt;strong&gt;Richard Branham&lt;/strong&gt;, sold 240 acres of land to Henry Austine on the North site of Rappahannock River and west s
2 CONC ite of Totaskey Creek. Wit: Thomas Gouldman, Tho. Short.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;5/3/1670 Rappahannock (now Richmond) Co VA Property Transfer &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li
2 CONC &gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Old Rappahannock County Deed Book (1668-1672), p 149:&lt;br&gt;3 May 1670, &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham&lt;/strong&gt; gives to his godson and cousin Thomas Freshwater a two-year old heifer. Wit. Will. Loyd
2 CONC , Edward Williams.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;30/8/1671 Rappahannock (now Richmond) Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&
2 CONC gt;Old Rappahannock Co., VA Deed Book (1668-1672), p 261-162:&lt;br&gt;30 of 8br 1671, Thomas Freshwater sells to &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham&lt;/strong&gt; 100 acres of woodland. With consent of wife Johanna Freshwater.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;
2 CONC li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;8/19/1691 Rappahannock Co VA Land Patent &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;On August 19, 1691, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Richard Branham&l
2 CONC t;/strong&gt; of Old Rappahannock County&amp;quot; received another patent consisting of &amp;quot;271 acres in the said county on the northwest side of Totaskey Creek, about a mile and a half from the mouth, by his own land&amp;quot; and that of R
2 CONC obert Syson, Nathaniel Thrift, and Cogwell.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;1692 Richmond and Essex Counties split from Rappahannock. [Rappahannock County became extin
2 CONC ct.] &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;1693 Richmond Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co., VA Deed Book 1, p. 9
2 CONC 6 Date 30 March 1693, Rec. 20 Dec. 1693:&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Richard Branham&lt;/strong&gt; of Farnham Parish, Richmond County to Thomas Gladman for 2000 lbs of tobacco, 100 acres of woodland. Adjoins land of Samuel Coggins and land of John Sher
2 CONC lock. With consent of Deborah, &amp;ldquo;my lawfull wife&amp;rdquo;. Witnesses: Wm Kissey, Robt (x) Thornton. Signed Richard Branham, Deborah (BB) Branham.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height
2 CONC : 100%" align="left"&gt;7/18/1710 Richmond Co VA Legal Proceeding &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co, VA Order Book 5, p. 188.Pounds vs. Bramham, 5 October 1710:&lt;br&gt;Bramham vs. Pound, 18 July 1710. In an act
2 CONC ion of debt between &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham&lt;/strong&gt;, Plt. and John Pound, Sr.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;10/5/1710 Richmond Co VA Legal Proceeding &l
2 CONC t;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co, VA Order Book 5, p. 211:&lt;br&gt;Barrow vs. Bramham&amp;rsquo;s Estate. 5 October 1710:&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham, Sr.&lt;/strong&gt; being arrested in an action o
2 CONC f case at the suit of John Pound, Jr. &lt;p&gt;Richmond Co., VA Order Book 5, p. 211:&lt;br&gt;Judgment being this day past unto John Pound, Jr. against Edward Barrow, Sherif, for the sume sued for nonappearance of &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham&lt;
2 CONC /strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;7/4/1711 Richmond Co VA Jury List &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co., VA Mis
2 CONC c. Records. p. 74 (Deed Book 5):&lt;br&gt;List of men to determine land dispute between William Woodbridge and Thomas Glascock: Andrew Dew, foreman, James Suggitt, John Gower, &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham&lt;/strong&gt;, Will Smoot, Job Hamon, Sr.
2 CONC , Fran. Lucas, Stanley Gower, Wm. Smith, David Berrick, Mark Tune, Fra. Yeats, William Thornton, surveyor. Dated. 2 July 1711. Rec. 4 July 1711.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align=
2 CONC "left"&gt;9/8/1712 Richmond Co VA Legal Proceeding &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co, VA Misc. Records, p. 75 (Deed Book 5):&lt;br&gt;When questioning Richard King, &amp;ldquo;an antient man and old stander in th
2 CONC ese parts&amp;rdquo;, they asked &amp;ldquo;Did you ever hear &lt;strong&gt;George Haslock dec&amp;rsquo;d&lt;/strong&gt; Grand Father to Tho. Freshwater say that the line which parted his land and the land of Tho. Robinson dec&amp;rsquo;d went b
2 CONC y his clear ground which was under the hill near the said Haslock&amp;rsquo;s house. . .&lt;strong&gt;Richard Branham&lt;/strong&gt;, &amp;ldquo;an Antient Man and Son in Law to Geo. Haslock, dec&amp;rsquo;d, Branham replied &amp;ldquo;No, George H
2 CONC aslock was dead before I came into the Countrey.&amp;rdquo; Sept. 8, 1712&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;Deborah died before 1714 in Richmond Co VA &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&
2 CONC gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;12/1714 Richmond Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co, VA Deed Book 7, pp. 15-16:&lt;br&gt;12/171
2 CONC 4 &lt;strong&gt;Richard Branham&lt;/strong&gt; to son John Branham, for love and affection, land part of patent granted to Richard, 271 acres. Witnesses John Gower, William Brockenbrough, Stanley Gower.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="m
2 CONC argin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;Married&amp;nbsp;12/1714 in Richmond Co VA to Ann Hobbs b. 1670 Rappahannock (now Essex) Co VA &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-he
2 CONC ight: 100%" align="left"&gt;12/1714 Richmond Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co. VA Deed Book 7, pp. 16-18:&lt;br&gt;12/1714 &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham&lt;/strong&gt;, Thomas Lewis, and T
2 CONC homas Thorne witness deed between Thomas Geffreys and William Hanks.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;4/2/1716 Richmond Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;
2 CONC /ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co., VA Deed Book 7, p. 113-114:&lt;br&gt;April 2, 1716. &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham Sr.&lt;/strong&gt; and Edmund Norden witness deed between William Garland of Westmoreland Co., and David Williams. Th
2 CONC e land bordered land belonging to Mrs. Anne Bramham formerly Green.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;5/1/1716 Richmond Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/l
2 CONC i&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond County, VA Deed Book 7, p. 123-125:&lt;br&gt;May 1, 1716. &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham&lt;/strong&gt; and John Taylor witness deed between Charles Barber and Rowland Lawson to Anthony Sydner.&lt;/
2 CONC div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;Will&amp;nbsp;dated 4/4/1728 in Richmond Co VA &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co., VA Will Book 5, p 95
2 CONC :&lt;br&gt;Will dated April 4, 1728, and proved on May 1, 1728, in which he refers to himself and &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Richard Branham, Senr.&lt;/strong&gt;, of the County of Richmond and Parish of North Farnham. Heirs were his son, Richard Bran
2 CONC ham, (a gun, a gold ring, and after the decease of his wife, the Plantation and all lands); his son, John Branham, (money); his loving wife, Ann Branham, (All the rest of his personal estate and the use of the plantation during her lifetime).&lt;br
2 CONC &gt;Executrix was his wife, Ann Branham&lt;br&gt;Witnesses were Robert Tomlin, Edward Gill, and Elizabeth Gill.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;3/16/1728 Richmond Co V
2 CONC A Legal Proceeding &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co., VA Deed Book 8, p 443-445:&lt;br&gt;16 March 1727/8, &lt;strong&gt;Richard Branham, Sr.&lt;/strong&gt;, &amp;ldquo;being very sick and uncapable of appearin
2 CONC g in person at Richmond Court&amp;rdquo;, gave power of attorney to friend Benjamin Rust to acknowledge deed to land to John Spendergrass. Witnessed by William Walker and Elizabeth Gill.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; mar
2 CONC gin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;3/16/1728 Richmond Co VA Land Transaction &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;Richmond Co., VA Deed Book 8, p 443-445:&lt;br&gt;16 March 1727/8, &lt;strong&gt;Richard Bramham
2 CONC , Sr.&lt;/strong&gt; to John Spendergrass 25 acres on which Bramham now lives. Witnessed by William Walker and Elizabeth Gill.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 100%" align="left"&gt;Died 5/1
2 CONC /1728 Richmond Co VA &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Children</line></content></metadataxml>
