2 TITL Dameron Damron Family Bio
1 _OID 5546e87f-cac3-4373-96c6-c7af75a38f89
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Moses Damron&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;c1735-c1812&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;(Moses Dameron) of Albemarl
2 CONC e and Russell Counties, Virginia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;A son of Lazarus Dameron &amp;amp; Elizabeth Smith&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="fo
2 CONC nt-size: small;"&gt;Moses' surname was recorded with each spelling. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Most of his children and descendants used DAMRON.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;s
2 CONC pan style="font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; He inherited his father's estate on Red Bank and Damron Creek, Albemarle County, Virginia. His plantation was near Scottsville, Virginia, not fa
2 CONC r from Peter Jefferson's plantation on the James River. Peter Jefferson was the father of Thomas Jefferson. Peter had purchased this property from Noble Ladd.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nb
2 CONC sp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Moses was involved in a land transaction recorded in Russell County deed records, page 1: "13 June 1786 James OSB
2 CONC URN and Mary, his wife, to Moses DAMRON for 100#, ...230A on waters of Clinch River ...from original patent to OSBURN dated 5 Jul 1785. Filed: 13 June 1787 ss: James Osburn Mary Osburn"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="fo
2 CONC nt-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Birth:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
2 CONC &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; ca __ ___ 1735&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Albemarle Co., Virginia.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;
2 CONC nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Marriage:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; ca __ ___ 1755&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;
2 CONC nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Death:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; ca __ ___ 1812&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Russell or Grayson Co., Virginia.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&l
