1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>3rd Cpl Leroy Allen.&amp;nbsp; (b. 1827) Lived in Tallahassee and enlisted 2/27/1862 at Camp Leon near Tallahassee. He was captured 9/17/1862 at Sharpsburg and was exchanged at Aikens Landing, VA.&amp;nbsp; He was promot
2 CONC ed to 3rd Sgt. on 10/1/1862 and was promoted again to 2nd Lt on 2/19/1863.&amp;nbsp; He was wounded at Cold Habor Creek, VA on June of 1864.&amp;nbsp; Was captured on 4/6/1865 at Sailor&amp;#39;s Creek, VA and was send to old Capitol Prison, Washin
2 CONC gton DC. then was send to Johnson&amp;#39;s Island on April 7, 1865.&amp;nbsp; He was released on Oath 6/18/1865 from Johnson&amp;#39;s Island near Sandusky, Ohio.&amp;nbsp; He was 6&amp;#39;1&amp;quot; with blue eyes, dark (skin) complexion and da
2 CONC rk hair.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Co. C, 5th&amp;nbsp;Florida Infantry - Confederate.&amp;nbsp;</line></content></metadataxml>
