2 TITL Biography
1 _OID 9527977b-e25a-462b-8163-402a5cc932b8
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;span style="font-family: tahoma, geneva, sans-serif"&gt;&lt;ul style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent
2 CONC : 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;div style="clear: both; width: 612px; word-wrap: break-word; : relative; display: inline-block; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Lazarus I
2 CONC I DAMERON&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: ini
2 CONC tial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;div style="width: 612px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc; text-align: ; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;div style="width: 612px
2 CONC ; border-width: 1px; border-color: #c7c1b6; border-style: solid; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;div style="padding: 12px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;p style="margin-: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-: 0px; line-height: 1.3; padding
2 CONC : 0px"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Lazarus Dameron of Albemarle County, Virginia, youngest Son of George and&lt;br&gt;Elizabeth Dameron, married Elizabeth Smith, Daughter of Richard Smith,&lt;br&gt;men
2 CONC tioned in his Will: Dated: 20 Nov 1721. Lazarus died in 1749.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; mar
2 CONC gin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Lazarus was the First Member of the Family to leave Northumberland&lt;br&gt;County. On 18 OCT 1726, he was Granted:&amp;nbsp;838 Acres of Land in King&lt;br&
2 CONC gt;George County. This Land, after 1730, lay in Prince William County.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note
2 CONC :&lt;/em&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Lazarus&amp;#39;s Will: Dated 1749 (MDCCXLIX), indicates,&amp;nbsp; he was then&lt;br&gt;living in the Parish of Anns, in the County of Albemarle. He bequeathed to&lt;br&gt;his son Mos
2 CONC es Dameron, &amp;quot;all my Houses and all my Land.&amp;quot;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em
2 CONC &gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Should Moses die without Heirs lawfully begotten, the Houses and Land&lt;br&gt;were to go to Lazarus&amp;#39;s Son, John.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-styl
2 CONC e-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Should John die without Heirs lawfully begotten, the Houses and Land&lt;br&gt
2 CONC ;were to go to Lazarus&amp;#39;s Daughter, Judith.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;bloc
2 CONC kquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Should Judith die without Heirs lawfully begotten, the Houses and Land&lt;br&gt;were to go to Lazarus&amp;#39;s Grandson, Charles Thomas.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-
2 CONC style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;Some furniture, tools, animals, books, and a rifle went to Moses.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-st
2 CONC yle-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&amp;quot;My boy John Ward&amp;quot; was given to Moses &amp;quot;for the r
2 CONC emaining part of his&lt;br&gt;Apprenticeship&amp;quot;. Should Moses die before the &amp;quot;Ward time&amp;quot; was up, Son,&lt;br&gt;John, got the Apprentice. (John also got &amp;quot;my second best bed&amp;quot;, and &amp;quot;my Boy&lt;br&gt;E
2 CONC nglish, under the experiation of his Apprenticeship.&amp;quot;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em
2 CONC &gt;&amp;nbsp;Judith received a bed and some furniture and a mare.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;blockqu
2 CONC ote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Daughter, Hanorah, received &amp;quot;my third best feather bed&amp;quot;, some furniture&lt;br&gt;and a mare.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-
2 CONC : initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;Son, George, received one shilling sterling.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-i
2 CONC mage: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Daughter, Winifred, Thomas also received one shilling. Son-in-law, John&lt;br&gt;Thomas, and Son, John Dameron were appointe
2 CONC d Executors of Estate.&lt;br&gt;******&lt;br&gt;(From Snow Book)&lt;br&gt;The original Farm of Lazarus Damron was in Porter&amp;#39;s Precinct, Albemarle&lt;br&gt;County. It was near the land which Peter Jefferson, Father of President&lt;br&gt;Thom
2 CONC as Jefferson, bought of Noble Ladd, on the James River -- then&lt;br&gt;called the Fluvanna, above where the Hardware River flows in it.&lt;br&gt;***&lt;br&gt;Lazarus was the First to sell his Ancestral Acres, and Pioneer into&lt;br&gt;Frontier Reg
2 CONC ions, as his descendants continued to do, until the Frontier&lt;br&gt;was pushed to the Pacific Ocean. In 1725, he Deeded his Land, and went to&lt;br&gt;Prince William, and King George Counties, and on to Albemarle County, Virginia,&lt;br&gt;wher
2 CONC e he died in 1749. Albemarle was then a Frontier, it became the&lt;br&gt;Cradle of Jeffersonian Democracy, which was to become a Fundamental&lt;br&gt;American Tadition after the Revolution.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0p
2 CONC x; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="text-indent: 0px; list-style-type: none; list-style-: initial; list-style-image: initial; pa
2 CONC dding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;&lt;blockquote style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px"&gt;Part of this revolution which was centered in Albemarle, and in Patrick Henry&amp;#39;s&lt;br&gt;Rregion nearby, wa
2 CONC s against the Established Church, a Movement led by&lt;br&gt;Patrick Henry, and Thomas Jefferson, of Albemarle. The Damerons appear&lt;br&gt;to have been active in this tradition, for many of them became strong&lt;br&gt;Baptists and Methodists, esp
2 CONC ecially the Families of the Revolutionary&lt;br&gt;Soldiers who pushed back the Fronteir. This Movement in the South was&lt;br&gt;similar to the Puritan Revolution in England 1642-1650, which&lt;br&gt;established a Commonwealth, until 1660, but th
2 CONC e Restoration brought&lt;br&gt;back part of the old regime. However, the Puritan churches still&lt;br&gt;controlled New England, chiefly Congregational, but also Presbyterian.&lt;br&gt;******&lt;br&gt;In 1749, Lazarus Dameron (often spelled; Damre
2 CONC l or Damerel), had a land&lt;br&gt;Grant on the North Side of the Upper James River. In 1746, he and his&lt;br&gt;Sons, John and George, had Surveys made at the same time.&lt;br&gt;******&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&l
2 CONC t;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
