1 _DSCR Confederate soldier. This is the first official flag of the Confederacy, called the "Stars and Bars," it was flown from 5 Mar 1861 to 26 May 1863. "The Confederate Flag" or "The Confederate Battle Flag" despite its never having historically represe
2 CONC nted the CSA as a nation, has become a widely recognized symbol of the South. It is often incorrectly referred to as the "Stars and Bars" (the actual "Stars and Bars" is the First National Flag).
