2 TITL John Hayes and family
1 _OID c970fa34-3e99-44b7-8a2d-7f1f57bdf375
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;John Hayes born Nov. 2, 1751, married Mary about 1772. John, Mary, and family emigrated from Virginia to Ninety-Six District of South Carolina, in the autumn of 1783. The first census was taken in 1790. The Joh
2 CONC n Hayes family, page 85, 1790 index, of Pendleton Co. SC lists one male older than sixteen, John was 39 at this time. It lists 2 males less than 16 yrs. Isaac B. was 8 yrs. at this time and younger brother Thomas. There were two females in the fami
2 CONC ly, his wife, Mary and a daughter. The John Hayes family is found in the 1800 census, on page 51, Pendleton Co. SC. It lists one male in 10&amp;lt;16 age, &amp;#39;Thomas&amp;#39;, one male in 16&amp;lt;26 age &amp;#39;Isaac B.&amp;#39; was 18 yrs
2 CONC , one male &amp;gt;45 yrs, &amp;#39;John&amp;#39; was 49yrs, one female 16&amp;lt;26 age group, daughter &amp;#39;Edie&amp;#39;, and one female 26&amp;gt;45, wife Mary. Mary was at least four years younger than John. The John Hayes family is on pag
2 CONC e 163 of the 1810 census of Pendleton Co. SC. Then in the 1820 census of Pendleton Co. SC page 197. The John Hayes and the Isaac B. Hayes (page 196) family, Isaac Hayes was born 1819. Isaac was 38 yrs. and wife Nancy is 37.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;John a
2 CONC nd Mary Hayes moved to Dekalb Co. GA in 1826, probably to live with youngest son, Thomas In the 1830 census of Anderson Co. SC on page 165, list the Isaac B. Hayes family with one male in 40&amp;lt;50 age. Isaac B. was 48 at this time. One female i
2 CONC n 40&amp;lt;50 age group, his wife Nancy was 47 at this time, two males in 10&amp;lt;15, Isaac and an older brother, Isaac was 10 or 11 at this time. In 1839 John and Mary died within a day of each other. On Monday night, June 17th 1839 John Haye
2 CONC s in his 88th year of age and on Wednesday evening at 2:00, June 19th, Mary died. They were members of the Methodist Episcopal Church for over 50 years. This is from Obituaries of S.C. The 1840 census of Anderson Co. S.C., the Isaac B. Hayes jamil
2 CONC y is found on page 128. Isaac was 58 yrs. and Nancy was 57 yrs.&amp;nbsp;Have not been able to locate the Isaac B. Hayes family in the 1850 census. Isaac B. may have died before th 1850 census and Nancy may have been living with their son Isaac. I
2 CONC n the 1860 census the Isaac Hayes family, is found in&amp;nbsp;Murray Co. Rocky Face, GA.&amp;nbsp;Nancy is&amp;nbsp;living with her son Isaac and is 77 yrs. old. Isaac&amp;#39;s first wife had died and his second, Hannabelle, had just given birt
2 CONC h to her first child several months earlier.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is believed that John&amp;#39;s son Thomas, had a plantation in Dekalb Co., near Atlanta GA. It is believed from the 1830 census of Dekalb Co., that John and Mary Hayes are living wi
2 CONC th Thomas and&amp;nbsp;his family. From the obituaries of S.C.&amp;nbsp;that they moved there in 1826 and that they died there in 1839. The 1830 census of Dekalb Co., GA shows that the Thomas Hayes family owned several slaves.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&l
2 CONC t;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
