2 TITL Captain Wm W Adkins
1 _OID d28a37f6-5df2-4b4e-b204-938681e6594c
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;In many family trees, William W Adkins married to Nancy Damron is often referred to as Captain, a rank that would have been obtained in the Civil War. Searching the Organization Index to Pension Files of Veteran
2 CONC s who served between 1861 and 1900, there are two matches for William W Adkins. One record shows that the company captain of the Richmond Company of the West Virginia Guards was William W. Adkins. Another record shows that a William W. Adkins serve
2 CONC d as a volunteer, but the regiment and company are blank.&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;Why would William Adkins from Floyd County, KY serve in a West Virginia regiment? Three of his sons, Jackson, Spurlock and Samuel were in the 39th Kentucky Mou
2 CONC nted Infantry Regiment. Jackson was a 2nd Lieutenant and the other two were privates.&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
