1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>Henry was a Sergeant in the Colonial Mitlitia and fought in the French  and Indian Wars.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Deed Book 1, pg 401-402: Boyle to Dooley&lt;br&gt;24  Apr 1761&lt;br&gt;Alexander Boyle of Bedford County sell
2 CONC s to Henry Dooley of  the same county 104 acres on the north side of Otter River adjacent to  Henry Dooly&amp;#39;s plantation for 50 pounds Current Money of Virginia.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Deed  Book 1, pg 488: 1761: Henry Dooley buys from Richard Ra
2 CONC ndolph, 200 acrs  on Harmon&amp;#39;s branch adjacent Adam Beard.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Heritage Book of  Bedford County 2003, pg 102: &amp;quot;Lived in Augusta Co, VA in 1764, but later  moved to Bedford Co, VA. Henry was a Sergeant in the Colon
2 CONC ial Milita  and fought in the French and Indian Wars.&amp;quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;17 June 1766: Henry  Dooley sells to Peter Harmon 200 acres N Fork of Otter River for 50  pounds, being pt patent of 400 acres grtd unto Alexander Boyle, dtd 26  Sep
2 CONC t 1760. B/S North fork Otter River.&lt;br&gt;Pres: Robt Ewing, Adam Beard,  Charles Ewing, Thomas Dooley, William Armstron, Michael Carns.</line></content></metadataxml>
