2 TITL Henry ADams
1 _OID fdafb4b4-157d-437f-b25f-6cedd5f8705b
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p style="text-align: center;" align="center"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;Information from Nancy Russell and her cousin Charles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line
2 CONC >&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;We wish to thank Nancy Russell and her cousin Charles for being so generous and allowing us to use the following information that she sent to us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</li
2 CONC ne><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Nancy Russell&amp;rsquo;s information:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><li
2 CONC ne>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;Yes, Grandpa Adams did kill Devil John&amp;rsquo;s son. Grandma&amp;rsquo;s story goes - &amp
2 CONC ;lsquo;she was a little girl coming home from school after a gully washer of a rain. They came to the creek which was too high for them to cross. About the time they reached the creek they noticed a group of men on horses on the other side of the c
2 CONC reek. One of them picked Grandma up and took her across the creek. He asked her who she was and she said Sarah Adams, Henry Adams&amp;rsquo; daughter. The man asked, &amp;ldquo; Where is your daddy?&amp;rdquo; She said, &amp;lsquo;he killed Johnn
2 CONC y Wright and we ain&amp;rsquo;t seen him since.&amp;rsquo; She told her mother about the incident to which her mother replied, &amp;lsquo;You little fool, that was Devil John and he was looking for your daddy."&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p
2 CONC &gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;Grandpa Adams was a fugitive for a period of time; running from Devil John who was a Kentucky sheriff at the time. Grandma&amp;rsquo;s mother died when she was 8 years old. Relatives divided the childre
2 CONC n up at the cemetery. It was 25 years before she seen one of her brothers. Eventually Grandpa went to prison, but eventually got out and remarried.&amp;nbsp; Nancy Russell&amp;rsquo;s cousin Charles said, &amp;ldquo;that grandma said it &lt;span st
2 CONC yle="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;(the cause of the trouble)&lt;/span&gt; was because Henry Adams was having an affair with Johnny&amp;rsquo;s wife and Johnny came to kill Henry Adams and he killed him in self-defense.&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="te
2 CONC xt-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; In the above information, Grandma is Sarah Ann Adams Wright, born 7 April 1890 at Jewell, Kentucky, was the daughter of Henry Adams and Eliza Jane Mullins. Sarah Ann stayed one winter with the f
2 CONC amily of cousin Charles and this is when she told cousin Charles the above details of what happened. The first school she attended was at Cane Branch. &lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;(Note that census records indicate that Sarah was born ca. 1
2 CONC 885. Also, Jewell was an early name for Shelby Gap.)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="fon
2 CONC t-size: 10pt;"&gt;Information from Joe Mize&amp;rsquo;s research:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The following is information from the late Joe Mize&amp;rsquo;s papers. Joe Mize was always very generous with any information h
2 CONC e had uncovered in all his research. We remember him with deep respect and are thankful he left us this information.&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10
2 CONC pt;"&gt;Joe&amp;rsquo;s information:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;Henry Adams (Booker Mullins&amp;rsquo; sister&amp;rsquo;s husband). He was big and fat. He killed Henderson &amp;ldquo;Hen&amp;rdquo; Mullins. His rifle wa
2 CONC s a 45-20 cl.&amp;nbsp; He called his rifle &amp;ldquo;Bone Crusher.&amp;rdquo; He killed 6 or 7 people. Henry Adams shot and killed Johnny P. Wright, son of Devil John Wright and Mattie Humphrey Wright in Jenkins. They were both riding horses an
2 CONC d Adams shot Johnny from under his horses neck&amp;ndash;this information came from Marvin &amp;ldquo;Moon&amp;rdquo; Mullins, Pulaski County, Kentucky.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="text-ali
2 CONC gn: center;" align="center"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;Tape recorded by Bonnie Caudill 1984 - Frank Wright, son of Johnny Wright (Goose Creek Frank).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p st
2 CONC yle="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Frank stated his father and Henry Adams were seeing the same lady friend and were jealous of each other. Johnny had been to see the lady who lived on Beefhide in Pike County, Kentucky. Henry Adam
2 CONC s was hidden behind a tree and shot him. Frank stated that love of whiskey and women was a big factor in his father&amp;rsquo;s death.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;div&gt;</line><line>&lt;
2 CONC p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Since this gun fight was such a news sensation locally, there were several other good sources from which we have obtained additional information, and from this wealth of information w
2 CONC e have been able to piece together a fairly detailed account of what happened on the day Henry Adams shot Johnny Wright to death in a gun fight. This is the first time a detailed account of this gun fight has ever been published. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbs
2 CONC p;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;/div&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
